Nine people were injured when a matatu they travelling in collided with a lorry.
 The accident occurred near Rambira trading centre in Rachuonyo North sub-county Sunday. The lorry was being driven from Katito while the matatu was from Kendu Bay town. 
 ALSO READ:

Seven dead in tragic road accident at Sultan Hamud (Photos)

 Witnesses said the incident occurred when the driver of the matatu lost control of the vehicle and it collided head-on with the oncoming lorry.
 “Both vehicles were travelling at a high speed before the accient,” said a witness.




